<subSubSection id="2D52396EC768B844302D4DF93DBABA1A" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph id="A7A4B65DB79937A6F0B476F360A2BBBD" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="95FBDF333905CA4577881F209DCD31E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Prothallus not seen. Thallus pale brownish-grey, continuous to rimose. Perithecia 0.12-0.21 mm, 3/4-immersed in thallus. Involucrellum apical, ca. 40-50 mm thick, appressed to the exciple. Exciple 0.27-0.33 mm in diam., wall black. Periphysoids ca. 40-45 
<normalizedToken id="D12DD41B3344DCA678DDE1D8432434FC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 mm. Ascospores 0-septate, 28-31 
<normalizedToken id="BD19FD04C7A1F9BF0F3273929B89172C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
12-15 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6AA3E633E3FB34B7EE288F49C33DA2DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph id="1967214A149A2DF2CA20961BD22AC250" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DA3654D7F87C8E3E23BFF7DAF7A42327" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
